entry.title: The Social Security (Shared Additional Pension) (Miscellaneous Amendments) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations make provision for claiming and paying Shared Additional Pension.

entry.title: The Fire (Scotland) Act 2005 (Relevant Premises) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations modify the definition of relevant premises in section 78 of the Fire (Scotland) Act 2005 by deleting the reference to construction sites in subsection (2)(b) and deleting subsection (2)(c). The effect of this is that, subject to the provisions of section 78(3), (6) and (7) of the 2005 Act, construction sites and premises which on 1st July 1999 were of a description specified in Part I of Schedule 1 to the Fire Certificates (Special Premises) Regulations 1976 (S.I. 1976/2003) are relevant premises for the purposes of Part 3 of the 2005 Act.

entry.title: Potatoes Originating in the Netherlands (Notification) (Revocation) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations revoke the Potatoes Originating in the Netherlands (Notification) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1999 (S.R. 1999 No. 1).

entry.title: The Dutch Potatoes (Notification) Order (Northern Ireland) 2005
entry.summary: This Order places certain notification requirements upon persons importing potatoes from the Netherlands which have been grown during 2004 or later.

title.div: The Contaminants in Food (Wales) (Amendment) Regulations 2005 / Rheoliadau Halogion mewn Bwyd (Cymru) (Diwygio) 2005

div.p: These Regulations, which apply in relation to Wales and amend the Contaminants in Food (Wales) Regulations 2005 (S.I. 2005/364 (W.31)) (the principal Regulations), provide for the enforcement of the requirements of Commission Regulation (EC) No 655/2004 amending Regulation (EC) No 466/2001 (OJ No L77, 16.3.2001, p.1) as regards nitrate in foods for infants and young children; andCommission Regulation (EC) No 683/2004 amending Regulation (EC) No 466/2001 as regards aflatoxins and ochratoxin A in foods for infants and young children.

Mae'r Rheoliadau hyn, sydd yn gymwys o ran Cymru, ac sy'n diwygio Rheoliadau Halogion mewn Bwyd (Cymru) 2005 (O.S. 2005/364 (Cy.31)) (y prif Reoliadau), yn darparu ar gyfer gorfodi gofynion Rheoliad y Comisiwn (EC) Rhif 655/2004 sy'n diwygio Rheoliad (EC) Rhif 466/2001 (OJ Rhif L77, 16.3.2001, t.1) o ran nitrad mewn bwydydd i fabanod a phlant ifanc; aRheoliad Comisiwn (EC) Rhif 683/2004 sy'n diwygio Rheoliad (EC) Rhif 466/2001 o ran afflatocsinau ac ocratocsin A mewn bwydydd i fabanod a phlant ifanc.

title.div: The Colours in Food (Amendment) (Wales) Regulations 2005 / Rheoliadau Lliwiau mewn Bwyd (Diwygio) (Cymru) 2005

div.p: These Regulations, which apply in relation to Wales, implement Commission Directive 2004/47/EC amending Directive 95/45/EC. They do so by further amending the Colours in Food Regulations 1995. The Regulations

Cyhoeddir y fersiwn hon o Rheoliadau Lliwiau mewn Bwyd (Diwygio) (Cymru) 2005 o dan awdurdod a goruchwyliaeth Argraffydd Deddfau Seneddol y Frenhines a Rheolwr Gwasg Ei Mawrhydi. Fe'i paratowyd i adlewyrchu'r testun fel y'i gwnaed.

entry.title: The Home Loss Payments (Prescribed Amounts)(England) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations increase the amount of home loss payments payable under section 30 of the Land Compensation Act 1973 (the Act) and formerly prescribed in the Home Loss Payments (Prescribed Amounts)(England) Regulations 2004. A person is entitled to a home loss payment when he is displaced from a dwelling by compulsory purchase or in the other circumstances specified in section 29 of the Act as last amended by the Planning and Compulsory Purchase Act 2004.

entry.title: The Water Services etc. (Scotland) Act 2005 (Commencement No. 1 and Savings) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order appoints 20th June and 1st July 2005 for the coming into force of certain of the provisions of the Water Services etc. (Scotland) Act 2005 (the 2005 Act), as set out in Schedules 1 and 2 of this Order.

entry.title: The Caledonian MacBrayne Limited (Kennacraig) Harbour Empowerment Order 2005
entry.summary: This version of the The Caledonian MacBrayne Limited (Kennacraig) Harbour Empowerment Order 2005 is published under the authority and superintendence of the Queen's Printer of Acts of Parliament and Controller of HMSO. It has been prepared to reflect the text as it was Made.

title.div: The National Health Service (Optical Charges and Payments) and (General Ophthalmic Services) (Amendment) (Wales) Regulations 2005 / Rheoliadau'r Gwasanaeth Iechyd Gwladol (Ffioedd a Thaliadau Optegol) a (Gwasanaethau Offthalmig Cyffredinol) (Diwygio) (Cymru) 2005

div.p: These Regulations further amend the National Health Service (Optical Charges and Payments) Regulations 1997 (the 1997 Regulations) and the National Health Service (General Ophthalmic Services) Regulations 1986 (the 1986 Regulations).

Mae'r Rheoliadau hyn yn diwygio ymhellach Reoliadau'r Gwasanaeth Iechyd Gwladol (Ffioedd a Thaliadau Optegol) 1997 (Rheoliadau 1997) a Rheoliadau'r Gwasanaeth Iechyd Gwladol (Gwasanaethau Offthalmig Cyffredinol) 1986 (Rheoliadau 1986).

entry.title: Industrial Training Levy (Construction Industry) Order (Northern Ireland) 2005
entry.summary: This Order gives effect to proposals submitted by the Construction Industry Training Board to the Department for Employment and Learning for the imposition of a further levy upon employers in the construction industry for the purpose of raising money towards the expenses of the Board.

entry.title: The Pension Protection Fund (Payments to meet Investment Costs) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations make provision for the Board of the Pension Protection Fund (the Board) to make payments from the Pension Protection Fund (the Fund) to fund managers or custodians in relation to contractual liabilities relating to the investment of the Fund. The contracts entered into must be necessary for the prudent management of the Fund.

entry.title: The St Nicholas CofE Primary School (Designation as having a Religious Character) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order designates St Nicholas CofE Primary School as having a religious character in accordance with section 69(3) of the School Standards and Framework Act 1998 (the Act).

entry.title: The Great Clacton Church of England Voluntary Aided Junior School (Designation as having a Religious Character) Order 2005
entry.summary: This Order designates Great Clacton Church of England Voluntary Aided Junior School as having a religious character in accordance with section 69(3) of the School Standards and Framework Act 1998 (the Act).

entry.title: The Health and Social Care (Community Health and Standards) Act 2003 (Public Health Laboratory Service Board) (Consequential Provisions) Order 2005

ukm:Subject.Value: NATIONAL HEALTH SERVICE, ENGLAND AND WALES

category.term: NATIONAL HEALTH SERVICE, ENGLAND AND WALES

entry.summary: This Order makes consequential provision in connection with the coming into force of section 190 of the Health and Social Care (Community Health and Standards) Act 2003 (the Act).

entry.title: The Education (Student Support) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations further amend the Education (Student Support) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2003 (the principal Regulations) as amended by the Education (Student Support) (Amendment) (No. 2) Regulations 2004 (the amending Regulations).

entry.title: Building (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations amend the Building Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2000 (the principal Regulations). They come into operation on 3rd October 2005. They do not apply to building work which has been completed, or for which plans or building notices have been deposited with a district council before that date.

entry.title: Contact Lens (Specification) and Sight Testing (Examination and Prescription) (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations set out the particulars which must be given to a patient by a medical practitioner when he issues a specification to a patient to whom he has fitted a contact lens.

entry.title: The Road Traffic Act 1988 (Retention and Disposal of Seized Motor Vehicles) Regulations 2005
entry.summary: Under section 165A of the Road Traffic Act 1988 (the 1988 Act) (retention etc of vehicle seized under section 165A) the police have certain powers to seize and remove motor vehicles. These Regulations provide for the retention, safe keeping and disposal by the police or persons authorised by them, of vehicles seized under those powers.

entry.title: General Ophthalmic Services (Amendment) Regulations (Northern Ireland) 2005
entry.summary: These Regulations further amend the General Ophthalmic Services Regulations (Northern Ireland) 1986 to make provision in relation to mobile services and for opticians to refer patients to a doctor within the hospital eye service and to so inform the patients doctor and give that patient a statement to that effect.
